
[1]shy

   SHY, a.

   1. Fearful of near approach; keeping at a distance through caution or
   timidity; shunning approach; as a shy bird.

   She is represented in a shy retiring posture. Addison.

   2. Reserved; not familiar; coy; avoiding freedom of intercourse.

   What makes you so shy, my good friend? Arbuthnot.

   3. Cautious; wary; careful to avoid committing one's self or adopting
   measures.

   I am very shy of using corrosive liquors in the preparation of
   medicines.
